p: Detailed interaction was evaluated to show the complexes were stabilized by many types of interaction ( Table 2). The docking process on spike protein did not use a native ligand due to lack of data in the protein data bank. Therefore, we explained the potential based on the docking score only. A conventional hydrogen bond has the main role to stabilize the interaction in the complexes. The result indicated that amino acids involved in the interaction are commonly similar.
